---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Origin of open clusters revealed by the evolution of the m_max - M_ecl relation - Zhou et al. (2026)";

import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Origin of open clusters revealed by the evolution of the m_max - M_ecl relation</h1>

    <div class="infobox">
      <h3 class="infobox-title">Zhou et al. (2026)</h3>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Type:</th>
          <td>Paper</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>First described:</th>
          <td>2026 (Zhou et al.)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>Key Papers:</th>
          <td>
            <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11782">Zhou+2026 (arXiv:2603.11782)</a>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Abstract summary:</strong> Gaia DR3 cluster catalog analysis and N-body simulations show that the evolution of the m_max–M_cluster relation supports subcluster coalescence as a dominant formation pathway for open clusters; coalescence models better reproduce observed deviations with age.</p>

    <h2>Key findings</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Observed m_max–M_cluster deviates with age; clusters >5 Myr show significant deviations</li>
      <li>Coalescence simulations match observations better than isolated cluster models</li>
      <li>Gas expulsion affects speed but not trajectory</li>
      <li>Supports subcluster coalescence as dominant formation mechanism</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="references">
      <h2>References</h2>
      <ol>
        <li id="ref1">Zhou, J. W., Dib, S., Kroupa, P. (2026). "Origin of open clusters revealed by the evolution of the m_max - M_ecl relation." <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11782">arXiv:2603.11782</a></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
